### **2.2 Bottom-Up Calculation Framework**

```
Bottom-Up TAM Formula:
TAM = (Target Population) Ã— (Average Annual Spending) Ã— (Market Penetration Rate)

Example Calculation:
â”œâ”€â”€ US Adults 18-65 who dine out: 200M people
â”œâ”€â”€ Average annual restaurant spending: $2,500
â”œâ”€â”€ Willing to pay for discovery service: 20%
â”œâ”€â”€ Average willingness to pay: $60/year
â””â”€â”€ TAM = 200M Ã— $60 Ã— 20% = $2.4B
```

