## ğŸ“Š **6. DATA VALIDATION & TRIANGULATION**

### **6.1 Cross-Reference Strategy**

#### **Validation Checklist:**
```
Data Verification:
â”œâ”€â”€ Compare 3+ sources for same metric
â”œâ”€â”€ Check publication dates (prefer <2 years old)
â”œâ”€â”€ Verify methodology and sample sizes
â”œâ”€â”€ Look for consistent growth rates across sources
â”œâ”€â”€ Validate with government data where possible
â”œâ”€â”€ Cross-check with public company financials
â””â”€â”€ Ensure geographic and demographic alignment
```

### **6.2 Red Flags to Watch For**

```
Data Quality Issues:
âŒ Single source for critical metrics
âŒ Outdated data (>3 years old)
âŒ Unclear methodology or sample size
âŒ Wildly different numbers across sources
âŒ No primary research backing
âŒ Overly optimistic growth projections
âŒ Conflating different market segments
```

